msgctxt "mn7:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 7 "
msgstr "Middle Discourses 7 "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: Vatthasutta → vatthū­pama­suttaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "mn7:0.2"
msgid "Vatthasutta "
msgstr "The Simile of the Cloth "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: nya1, sc1
msgctxt "mn7:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "mn7:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. "

msgctxt "mn7:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: "
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants, "

msgctxt "mn7:1.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti. "
msgstr "“Mendicants!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn7:1.5"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ. "
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied. "

msgctxt "mn7:1.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said this: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya2, sc2
msgctxt "mn7:2.1"
msgid "“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, vatthaṃ saṃkiliṭṭhaṃ malaggahitaṃ; "
msgstr "“Suppose, mendicants, there was a cloth that was dirty and soiled. "

#. VAR: mañjiṭṭhakāya → mañjeṭṭhakāya (bj, pts1) | mañjeṭṭhikāya (s1-3)
msgctxt "mn7:2.2"
msgid "tamenaṃ rajako yasmiṃ yasmiṃ raṅgajāte upasaṃhareyya—yadi nīlakāya yadi pītakāya yadi lohitakāya yadi mañjiṭṭhakāya durattavaṇṇamevassa aparisuddhavaṇṇamevassa. "
msgstr "No matter what dye the dyer applied—whether yellow or red or magenta—it would look poorly dyed and impure in color. "

msgctxt "mn7:2.3"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "mn7:2.4"
msgid "Aparisuddhattā, bhikkhave, vatthassa. "
msgstr "Because of the impurity of the cloth. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn7:2.5"
msgid "Evameva kho, bhikkhave, citte saṃkiliṭṭhe, duggati pāṭikaṅkhā. "
msgstr "In the same way, when the mind is corrupt, a bad destiny is to be expected. "

msgctxt "mn7:2.6"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, vatthaṃ parisuddhaṃ pariyodātaṃ; "
msgstr "Suppose there was a cloth that was pure and clean. "

msgctxt "mn7:2.7"
msgid "tamenaṃ rajako yasmiṃ yasmiṃ raṅgajāte upasaṃhareyya—yadi nīlakāya yadi pītakāya yadi lohitakāya yadi mañjiṭṭhakāya—surattavaṇṇamevassa parisuddhavaṇṇamevassa. "
msgstr "No matter what dye the dyer applied—whether yellow or red or magenta—it would look well dyed and pure in color. "

msgctxt "mn7:2.8"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "mn7:2.9"
msgid "Parisuddhattā, bhikkhave, vatthassa. "
msgstr "Because of the purity of the cloth. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn7:2.10"
msgid "Evameva kho, bhikkhave, citte asaṃkiliṭṭhe, sugati pāṭikaṅkhā. "
msgstr "In the same way, when the mind isn’t corrupt, a good destiny is to be expected. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya3, pts-vp-pli1.37, sc3
msgctxt "mn7:3.1"
msgid "Katame ca, bhikkhave, cittassa upakkilesā? "
msgstr "And what are the corruptions of the mind? "

msgctxt "mn7:3.2"
msgid "Abhijjhāvisamalobho cittassa upakkileso, byāpādo cittassa upakkileso, kodho cittassa upakkileso, upanāho cittassa upakkileso, makkho cittassa upakkileso, paḷāso cittassa upakkileso, issā cittassa upakkileso, macchariyaṃ cittassa upakkileso, māyā cittassa upakkileso, sāṭheyyaṃ cittassa upakkileso, thambho cittassa upakkileso, sārambho cittassa upakkileso, māno cittassa upakkileso, atimāno cittassa upakkileso, mado cittassa upakkileso, pamādo cittassa upakkileso. "
msgstr "Covetousness and immoral greed, ill will, anger, hostility, offensiveness, contempt, jealousy, stinginess, deceit, deviousness, obstinacy, aggression, conceit, arrogance, vanity, and negligence are corruptions of the mind. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
