#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "mn7:5.32"
msgid "So buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti: "
msgstr "they have experiential confidence in the Buddha: "

msgctxt "mn7:5.33"
msgid "‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti; "
msgstr "‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya6
msgctxt "mn7:6.1"
msgid "dhamme aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti: "
msgstr "They have experiential confidence in the teaching: "

msgctxt "mn7:6.2"
msgid "‘svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo sandiṭṭhiko akāliko ehipassiko opaneyyiko paccattaṃ veditabbo viññūhī’ti; "
msgstr "‘The teaching is well explained by the Buddha—visible in this very life, immediately effective, inviting inspection, relevant, so that sensible people can know it for themselves.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya7
msgctxt "mn7:7.1"
msgid "saṅghe aveccappasādena samannāgato hoti: "
msgstr "They have experiential confidence in the Saṅgha: "

msgctxt "mn7:7.2"
msgid "‘suppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho, ujuppaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho, ñāyappaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho, sāmīcippaṭipanno bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho, yadidaṃ cattāri purisayugāni, aṭṭha purisapuggalā. Esa bhagavato sāvakasaṅgho āhuneyyo pāhuneyyo dakkhiṇeyyo añjalikaraṇīyo, anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassā’ti. "
msgstr "‘The Saṅgha of the Buddha’s disciples is practicing the way that’s good, straightforward, methodical, and proper. It consists of the four pairs, the eight individuals. This is the Saṅgha of the Buddha’s disciples that is worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, worthy of greeting with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the world.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya8-11, pts-vp-pli1.38, sc7
#. VAR: Yathodhi → yatopi (bj) | yatodhi (aṭṭhakathāyaṃ pāṭhantaraṃ)
msgctxt "mn7:8-11.1"
msgid "Yathodhi kho panassa cattaṃ hoti vantaṃ muttaṃ pahīnaṃ paṭinissaṭṭhaṃ, so ‘buddhe aveccappasādena samannāgatomhī’ti labhati atthavedaṃ, labhati dhammavedaṃ, labhati dhammūpasaṃhitaṃ pāmojjaṃ. "
msgstr "When a mendicant has discarded, eliminated, released, given up, and relinquished to this extent, thinking, ‘I have experiential confidence in the Buddha … "

msgctxt "mn7:8-11.2"
msgid "Pamuditassa pīti jāyati, pītimanassa kāyo passambhati, passaddhakāyo sukhaṃ vedeti, sukhino cittaṃ samādhiyati; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn7:8-11.3"
msgid "‘dhamme … pe … "
msgstr "the teaching … "

msgctxt "mn7:8-11.4"
msgid "saṃghe aveccappasādena samannāgatomhī’ti labhati atthavedaṃ, labhati dhammavedaṃ, labhati dhammūpasaṃhitaṃ pāmojjaṃ; "
msgstr "the Saṅgha,’ they find joy in the meaning and the teaching, and find joy connected with the teaching. "

msgctxt "mn7:8-11.5"
msgid "pamuditassa pīti jāyati, pītimanassa kāyo passambhati, passaddhakāyo sukhaṃ vedeti, sukhino cittaṃ samādhiyati. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn7:8-11.6"
msgid "‘Yathodhi kho pana me cattaṃ vantaṃ muttaṃ pahīnaṃ paṭinissaṭṭhan’ti labhati atthavedaṃ, labhati dhammavedaṃ, labhati dhammūpasaṃhitaṃ pāmojjaṃ; "
msgstr "Thinking: ‘I have discarded, eliminated, released, given up, and relinquished to this extent,’ they find joy in the meaning and the teaching, and find joy connected with the teaching. "

msgctxt "mn7:8-11.7"
msgid "pamuditassa pīti jāyati, pītimanassa kāyo passambhati, passaddhakāyo sukhaṃ vedeti, sukhino cittaṃ samādhiyati. "
msgstr "When they’re joyful, rapture springs up. When the mind is full of rapture, the body becomes tranquil. When the body is tranquil, they feel bliss. And when they’re blissful, the mind becomes immersed in samādhi. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya12, sc8
msgctxt "mn7:12.1"
msgid "Sa kho so, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃsīlo evaṃdhammo evaṃpañño sālīnañcepi piṇḍapātaṃ bhuñjati vicitakāḷakaṃ anekasūpaṃ anekabyañjanaṃ, nevassa taṃ hoti antarāyāya. "
msgstr "When a mendicant of such ethics, such qualities, and such wisdom eats boiled fine rice with the dark grains picked out and served with many soups and sauces, that is no obstacle for them. "

msgctxt "mn7:12.2"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, vatthaṃ saṅkiliṭṭhaṃ malaggahitaṃ acchodakaṃ āgamma parisuddhaṃ hoti pariyodātaṃ, ukkāmukhaṃ vā panāgamma jātarūpaṃ parisuddhaṃ hoti pariyodātaṃ; "
msgstr "Compare with cloth that is dirty and soiled; it can be made pure and clean by pure water. Or unrefined gold, which can be made pure and bright by a forge. "

msgctxt "mn7:12.3"
msgid "evameva kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu evaṃsīlo evaṃdhammo evaṃpañño sālīnañcepi piṇḍapātaṃ bhuñjati vicitakāḷakaṃ anekasūpaṃ anekabyañjanaṃ, nevassa taṃ hoti antarāyāya. "
msgstr "In the same way, when a mendicant of such ethics, such qualities, and such wisdom eats boiled fine rice with the dark grains picked out and served with many soups and sauces, that is no obstacle for them. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya13-16, sc9
#. VAR: catutthaṃ → catutthiṃ (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "mn7:13-16.1"
msgid "So mettāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharati, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ. Iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ mettāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyāpajjena pharitvā viharati; "
msgstr "They meditate spreading a heart full of love to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of love to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will. "

msgctxt "mn7:13-16.2"
msgid "karuṇāsahagatena cetasā … pe … "
msgstr "They meditate spreading a heart full of compassion to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of compassion to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will. "

msgctxt "mn7:13-16.3"
msgid "muditāsahagatena cetasā … pe … "
msgstr "They meditate spreading a heart full of rejoicing to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of rejoicing to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will. "

msgctxt "mn7:13-16.4"
msgid "upekkhāsahagatena cetasā ekaṃ disaṃ pharitvā viharati, tathā dutiyaṃ, tathā tatiyaṃ, tathā catutthaṃ. Iti uddhamadho tiriyaṃ sabbadhi sabbattatāya sabbāvantaṃ lokaṃ upekkhāsahagatena cetasā vipulena mahaggatena appamāṇena averena abyāpajjena pharitvā viharati. "
msgstr "They meditate spreading a heart full of equanimity to one direction, and to the second, and to the third, and to the fourth. In the same way above, below, across, everywhere, all around, they spread a heart full of equanimity to the whole world—abundant, expansive, limitless, free of enmity and ill will. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya17, pts-vp-pli1.39, sc10
msgctxt "mn7:17.1"
msgid "So ‘atthi idaṃ, atthi hīnaṃ, atthi paṇītaṃ, atthi imassa saññāgatassa uttari nissaraṇan’ti pajānāti. "
msgstr "They understand: ‘There is this, there is what is worse than this, there is what is better than this, and there is an escape beyond the scope of perception.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya18
msgctxt "mn7:18.1"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ jānato evaṃ passato kāmāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati, bhavāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati, avijjāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccati. "
msgstr "Knowing and seeing like this, their mind is freed from the defilements of sensuality, desire to be reborn, and ignorance. "

msgctxt "mn7:18.2"
msgid "Vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti. "
msgstr "When they’re freed, they know they’re freed. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn7:18.3"
msgid "‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti pajānāti. "
msgstr "They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’ "

msgctxt "mn7:18.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave: "
msgstr "This is called "

msgctxt "mn7:18.5"
msgid "‘bhikkhu sināto antarena sinānenā’”ti. "
msgstr "a mendicant who is bathed with the inner bathing.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya19, sc11
msgctxt "mn7:19.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena sundarikabhāradvājo brāhmaṇo bhagavato avidūre nisinno hoti. "
msgstr "Now, at that time the brahmin Sundarika Bhāradvāja was sitting not far from the Buddha. "

msgctxt "mn7:19.2"
msgid "Atha kho sundarikabhāradvājo brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "He said to the Buddha, "

msgctxt "mn7:19.3"
msgid "“gacchati pana bhavaṃ gotamo bāhukaṃ nadiṃ sināyitun”ti? "
msgstr "“But does Master Gotama go to the river Bāhuka to bathe?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn7:19.4"
msgid "“Kiṃ, brāhmaṇa, bāhukāya nadiyā? "
msgstr "“Brahmin, why go to the river Bāhuka? "

msgctxt "mn7:19.5"
msgid "Kiṃ bāhukā nadī karissatī”ti? "
msgstr "What can the river Bāhuka do?” "

# NOTE: BB has “liberation”, obviously following PTS in reading “mokkhasammata”. This reading is supported by MA 93, which has 度相. (The other Chinese parallel at T 51 doesn’t have a close parallel with this phrase.) However the comm evidently reads lokkha: Tattha lokkhasammatāti lūkhabhāvasammatā, lūkhabhāvanti cokkhabhāvaṃ, visuddhibhāvaṃ detīti evaṃ sammatāti vuttaṃ hoti. The problem is that lokkha gives the exact opposite sense: rough or dirty. Nor does there appear to be any supporting sense in Sanskrit. The PTS dict suggests reading cokkha=clean here: https://suttacentral.net/define/cokkha, and I think this is the best reading. Liberation doesn’t fit the imagery of the text. Nor, so far as I know, was it generally held among the brahmins that liberation came from bathing alone. On the contrary, it is precisely those brahmins who developed the notion of liberation who insisted on the inner understanding. I suspect the Chinese translation, therefore, is a normalization, as is the reading mokkha in the Pali.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: Lokkhasammatā → lokhyasammatā (bj) | lokasammatā (s1-3) | mokkhasammatā (pts1)
msgctxt "mn7:19.6"
msgid "“Lokkhasammatā hi, bho gotama, bāhukā nadī bahujanassa, puññasammatā hi, bho gotama, bāhukā nadī bahujanassa, bāhukāya pana nadiyā bahujano pāpakammaṃ kataṃ pavāhetī”ti. "
msgstr "“Many people agree that the river Bāhuka bestows cleanliness and merit. And many people wash off their bad deeds in the river Bāhuka.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya20
msgctxt "mn7:20.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā sundarikabhāradvājaṃ brāhmaṇaṃ gāthāhi ajjhabhāsi: "
msgstr "Then the Buddha addressed Sundarika in verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "mn7:20.2"
msgid "“Bāhukaṃ adhikakkañca, "
msgstr "“The Bāhuka and the Adhikakka, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: sundarikaṃ mapi → sundarikāmapi (bj, s1-3, pts1) | sundarikaṃ mahiṃ (itipi)
msgctxt "mn7:20.3"
msgid "gayaṃ sundarikaṃ mapi; "
msgstr "the Gaya and the Sundarika too, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn7:20.4"
msgid "Sarassatiṃ payāgañca, "
msgstr "Sarasvatī and Payāga, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn7:20.5"
msgid "atho bāhumatiṃ nadiṃ; "
msgstr "and the river Bāhumati: "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: pakkhando → pakkhanno (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "mn7:20.6"
msgid "Niccampi bālo pakkhando, "
msgstr "a fool can constantly plunge into them "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn7:20.7"
msgid "kaṇhakammo na sujjhati. "
msgstr "but it won’t purify their dark deeds. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "mn7:20.8"
msgid "Kiṃ sundarikā karissati, "
msgstr "What can the Sundarika do? "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: payāgā → payāgo (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "mn7:20.9"
msgid "Kiṃ payāgā kiṃ bāhukā nadī; "
msgstr "What the Payāga or the Bāhuka? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn7:20.10"
msgid "Veriṃ katakibbisaṃ naraṃ, "
msgstr "They can’t cleanse a cruel and criminal person "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn7:20.11"
msgid "Na hi naṃ sodhaye pāpakamminaṃ. "
msgstr "from their bad deeds. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "mn7:20.12"
msgid "Suddhassa ve sadā phaggu, "
msgstr "For the pure in heart it’s always "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn7:20.13"
msgid "Suddhassuposatho sadā; "
msgstr "the spring festival or the sabbath. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn7:20.14"
msgid "Suddhassa sucikammassa, "
msgstr "For the pure in heart and clean of deed, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn7:20.15"
msgid "Sadā sampajjate vataṃ; "
msgstr "their vows will always be fulfilled. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn7:20.16"
msgid "Idheva sināhi brāhmaṇa, "
msgstr "It’s here alone that you should bathe, brahmin, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn7:20.17"
msgid "Sabbabhūtesu karohi khemataṃ. "
msgstr "making yourself a sanctuary for all creatures. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc15
msgctxt "mn7:20.18"
msgid "Sace musā na bhaṇasi, "
msgstr "And if you speak no lies, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn7:20.19"
msgid "sace pāṇaṃ na hiṃsasi; "
msgstr "nor harm any living creature, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn7:20.20"
msgid "Sace adinnaṃ nādiyasi, "
msgstr "nor steal anything not given, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn7:20.21"
msgid "saddahāno amaccharī; "
msgstr "and you’re faithful and not stingy: "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn7:20.22"
msgid "Kiṃ kāhasi gayaṃ gantvā, "
msgstr "what’s the point of going to Gaya? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn7:20.23"
msgid "udapānopi te gayā”ti. "
msgstr "For any well will be your Gaya!” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: nya21, pts-vp-pli1.40, sc16
msgctxt "mn7:21.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, sundarikabhāradvājo brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he had spoken, the brahmin Sundarika Bhāradvāja said to the Buddha, "

msgctxt "mn7:21.2"
msgid "“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama, abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama. "
msgstr "“Excellent, Master Gotama! Excellent! "

msgctxt "mn7:21.3"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bho gotama, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya—cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantīti; evamevaṃ bhotā gotamena anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito. "
msgstr "As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good eyes can see what’s there, Master Gotama has made the teaching clear in many ways. "

msgctxt "mn7:21.4"
msgid "Esāhaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca. "
msgstr "I go for refuge to Master Gotama, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha. "

msgctxt "mn7:21.5"
msgid "Labheyyāhaṃ bhoto gotamassa santike pabbajjaṃ, labheyyaṃ upasampadan”ti. "
msgstr "Sir, may I receive the going forth, the ordination in the Buddha’s presence?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya22
msgctxt "mn7:22.1"
msgid "Alattha kho sundarikabhāradvājo brāhmaṇo bhagavato santike pabbajjaṃ, alattha upasampadaṃ. "
msgstr "And the brahmin Sundarika Bhāradvāja received the going forth, the ordination in the Buddha’s presence. "

msgctxt "mn7:22.2"
msgid "Acirūpasampanno kho panāyasmā bhāradvājo eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto ātāpī pahitatto viharanto nacirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsi. "
msgstr "Not long after his ordination, Venerable Bhāradvāja, living alone, withdrawn, diligent, keen, and resolute, soon realized the supreme end of the spiritual path in this very life. He lived having achieved with his own insight the goal for which gentlemen rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn7:22.3"
msgid "“Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā”ti abbhaññāsi. "
msgstr "He understood: “Rebirth is ended; the spiritual journey has been completed; what had to be done has been done; there is no return to any state of existence.” "

msgctxt "mn7:22.4"
msgid "Aññataro kho panāyasmā bhāradvājo arahataṃ ahosīti. "
msgstr "And Venerable Bhāradvāja became one of the perfected. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn7:22.5"
msgid "Vatthasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ sattamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

